cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.HC 

This paper deals with the problem of procedurally generating quests in text-adventure games, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves game theory and human-computer interaction, which could place it in the categories cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), respectively.
